Persian Gulf Stocks: Abu Dhabi National Energy, Saudi Hotels

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-08-09T13:56:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/persian-gulf-stocks-abu-dhabi-national-energy-saudi-hotels.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  declined 2
percent to 1,444.29, the lowest level since March 9, at the 2
p.m. close in the emirate. Abu Dhabi’s gauge lost 1.3 percent
and Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX)  fell 0.8 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.        Abu Dhabi National Energy Co. (TAQA)   slumped to the
lowest level since May 26, losing 3.3 percent to 1.17 dirhams.
The state-run utility known as Taqa had its Bergermeer
underground gas storage project temporarily suspended by the
Dutch Council of State pending a review of objections by parties
including local authorities.        Saudi Hotels & Resort Areas Co. (SHARCO)   surged the most
since March 6, advancing 7.3 percent to 28 riyals. The operator
of hotels and housing compounds plans to raise its capital by 45
percent to 1 billion riyals ($266 million) from 690 million
riyals, it said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
